  , issueCommentBody =
      "@neumino suggested a couple of commands in https://github.com/rethinkdb/company/issues/17#issuecomment-37899006:\r\n\r\nAdd methods like  `updateField`, `deleteWhere`, `updateWhere` (we would have to find better names)\r\n\r\nAdd an element in a field\r\n```\r\nr.table(\"posts\").updateField(\"comments\", function(comments) {\r\n    return comments.append({author: \"Michel\", comment: \"Hello\" })\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nDelete an element in an array\r\n```\r\nr.table(\"posts\").updateField(\"comments\", function(comments) {\r\n    return comments.deleteWhere(function(comment) {\r\n        comment(\"author\").eq(\"Michel\")\r\n    })\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nUpdate an element in an array\r\n```\r\nr.table(\"posts\").updateField(\"comments\", function(comments) {\r\n    return comments.updateWhere(\r\n        function(comment) { return comment(\"author\").eq(\"Michel\") },\r\n        function(comment) { return comment.updateField(\"author\", \"Michel T.\") }\r\n     )\r\n})\r\n```\r\nThe point of `updateField` is to easily update a nested field without having to do tons of `map`/`do`/`merge` (so the first argument can be `{nested: {field: true}}`\r\nThis syntax is close to Mongo's one, and we would provide something better in some cases -- e.g: https://jira.mongodb.org/browse/SERVER-1243\r\n\r\nMarking as proposal."
